pany would attract a broad range of investors world business briefing  africa south africa gold miner posts a loss the harmony gold mining company which has bid to take over gold fields to become the worlds biggest gold producer posted a loss of  million rand  million in its most recent quarter its fifth consecutive quarterly loss the loss in its first quarter which ended sept  was smaller than the loss of  million rand in the fourth quarter as the company cut jobs and shut unprofitable mine shafts the company lost  million rand in the yearearlier quarter separately gold fields said it would respond to harmonys  billion takeover bid on nov  south african miner in hostile bid for gold fields harmony gold mining the largest miner of south african gold made a hostile bid yesterday to acquire gold fields ltd another south african miner for  billion rand  billion in stock igniting a bitter takeover battle to create the worlds largest gold producer gold fields with extensive worldwide holdings is twice the size of harmony the unsolicited offer could derail a  billion merger deal reached in the summer to combine gold fields and iamgold of canada gold fields to buy iamgold fending off bidder from us gold fields the large gold producer based in johannesburg agreed wednesday to buy the iamgold corporation based in toronto in a stock swap valued at about  billion fending off a competing bid from golden star resources iamgold will issue  million shares and become part of a new publicly traded gold fields unit led by gordon r parker  the former chairman of the newmont mining corporation russians buy gold fields mining stake norilsk nickel said on monday that it had acquired  percent of gold fields the south african mining corporation from angloamerican for  billion in cash the move which took the industry by surprise propels norilsk a large russian metals producer little known in the west into the top ranks of gold producers norilsk nickel believes the purchase of a  percent stake in gold fields with its worldclass gold mining assets to be an excellent investment leonid rozhetskin vice chairman for the management board of norilsk nickel said in a written statement we think particularly highly of gold fields management black group in south africa to buy stake in gold mines gold fields one of the worlds largest gold miners said yesterday that it had agreed to sell a  percent stake in its south african operations to mvelaphanda resources for  billion rand  million the transaction is one of the biggest so far in south africas sixyear effort to expand the role of blacks in owning and operating the countrys gold industry through this deal we will speedily achieve our stated objectives of putting together a black economic transaction which will transform gold fields ian cockerill the chief executive of gold fields said in a statement to the securities exchange news service in johannesburg where the company is based company news anglo american to acquire stakes in  mining rivals anglo american one of the worlds largest mining companies has agreed to trade  million in nonmining assets for minority stakes in two competitors anglo will turn over threequarters of its  percent stake in firstrand a major south african financial services company to remgro a holding company for mining financial and industrial interests in exchange it will get  percent of billiton and  percent of gold fields anglo has shed assets worth about  billion this year to concentrate on mining and processing ore world business briefing africa profit grows at gold fields ltd helped by improved efficiency at its mines and a decline in the value of the south african rand gold fields ltd the worlds thirdlargest producer of gold reported that quarterly profits more than tripled to  million rand or  million the performance was considered especially strong in light of the languishing price of gold gold fields has agreed to merge with the franconevada mining corporation of canada and move its primary stock listing from johannesburg to toronto but the merger has yet to be approved by south africa henri e cauvin international business a south africancanadian merger in gold gold fields ltd became the first south african gold producer to merge with a foreign counterpart today a deal with the franconevada mining corporation of canada creating a mining giant with a combined market value of  billion the transaction partly reflects the global pressure on gold producers to combine and keep costs low best positioning themselves for the possibility that the prolonged slump in gold prices will end world business briefing africa mine strike threatened south africas gold industry the worlds biggest faces a nationwide strike in as little as two weeks unless managers retract plans to dismiss workers the countrys biggest mining union said the national union of mineworkers threatened to expand a sevenday strike by  miners to protest proposed job cuts at gold fields ltd the worlds secondbiggest gold company to include as many as  workers nationwide south african gold companies which have the highest average production costs in the industry need to cut more than  jobs to survive with prices at a year low the chamber of mines says gold field purchase london dec  reutersrecent market purchases have raised the stake in consolidated gold fields ltd held by de beers consolidated mines ltd and the anglo american corporation  company news largest gold miner buys stake in rival penn central agrees to bond settlement bethlehem raising steel plate prices london catholic bishops to sell stock in company with south african mines london thursday july  ap the roman catholic archdiocese of westminster announced today that it was selling  worth of stock in a british company that the archdiocese accuses of responsibility for racial injustices at its mines in south africa two financiers get prison in capetown writs halt  companies sec reports consent decrees entered in montana cases the 